<div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6 py-16">
  <div class="mb-12">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight text-gray-900">Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-gray-500">Effective date: April 10, 2026</p>
    <div class="mt-4 h-px bg-gray-200"></div>
  </div>

  <div class="space-y-10 text-sm leading-relaxed text-gray-700">

    <section>
      <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">Introduction</h2>
      <p>Tikedon ("we," "us," "our") operates a software application that integrates with TikTok Shop's Partner API to provide affiliate outreach management services. This Privacy Policy describes how we collect, use, store, share, and protect information when you use our application. By using Tikedon, you agree to the practices described in this policy.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">Information we collect</h2>

      <div class="mt-4 rounded-lg border border-gray-200 bg-gray-50 p-5">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Information you provide</h3>
        <ul class="space-y-2 list-disc pl-5">
          <li><strong>Account information:</strong> name, email address, and password when you register for a Tikedon account.</li>
          <li><strong>Business information:</strong> shop name, product catalog details, campaign configurations, commission rates, and outreach message content that you create within the application.</li>
          <li><strong>Authorization credentials:</strong> when you connect a TikTok Shop seller account through OAuth, we receive authorization tokens that allow us to make API requests on your behalf.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-4 rounded-lg border border-gray-200 bg-gray-50 p-5">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Information received from TikTok Shop</h3>
        <ul class="space-y-2 list-disc pl-5">
          <li><strong>Creator profile data:</strong> publicly available information about TikTok creators retrieved through TikTok Shop's official API, including display names, follower counts, content categories, and performance metrics.</li>
          <li><strong>Order and fulfillment data:</strong> order status and delivery information related to affiliate sample fulfillment.</li>
          <li><strong>Collaboration data:</strong> status of affiliate invitations, collaboration responses, and campaign performance metrics.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-4 rounded-lg border border-gray-200 bg-gray-50 p-5">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Information collected automatically</h3>
        <ul class="space-y-2 list-disc pl-5">
          <li><strong>Usage information:</strong> features accessed, actions taken within the application, and service usage metrics.</li>
          <li><strong>Technical information:</strong> IP address, browser type, and device information transmitted with each request.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">How we use your information</h2>
      <div class="overflow-hidden rounded-lg border border-gray-200">
        <table class="min-w-full text-sm">
          <thead class="bg-gray-50">
            <tr>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-900">Purpose</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-900">Description</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody class="divide-y divide-gray-100">
            <tr>
              <td class="px-4 py-3 font-medium text-gray-900">Provide services</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-3">Authenticate your account, connect to TikTok Shop on your behalf, search and display creator information, send collaboration invitations, manage samples, and track campaign performance.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="px-4 py-3 font-medium text-gray-900">Content compliance</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-3">Review outreach messages for compliance with TikTok Shop's content policies before they are sent.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="px-4 py-3 font-medium text-gray-900">Service improvement</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-3">Analyze usage patterns to improve application functionality and reliability.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="px-4 py-3 font-medium text-gray-900">Communication</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-3">Respond to support requests and send service-related notifications.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="px-4 py-3 font-medium text-gray-900">Security</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-3">Detect and prevent unauthorized access, fraud, and abuse.</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">How we share your information</h2>
      <p class="mb-4">We do <strong class="text-gray-900">not</strong> sell, rent, or trade your personal information. We share information only in the following circumstances:</p>
      <ul class="space-y-3 list-disc pl-5">
        <li><strong>TikTok Shop:</strong> We transmit data to TikTok Shop through their official Partner API as authorized by you through the OAuth connection. TikTok's own privacy policy governs how they handle data on their platform.</li>
        <li><strong>Service providers:</strong> We use third-party service providers that assist with content quality review, hosting, and infrastructure. These providers process data solely on our behalf and are contractually obligated to protect your information.</li>
        <li><strong>Legal requirements:</strong> We may disclose information if required to do so by law, regulation, legal process, or governmental request.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">Data security</h2>
      <p class="mb-4">We implement appropriate technical and organizational measures to protect your information:</p>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 gap-3 sm:grid-cols-2">
        <div class="rounded-lg border border-gray-200 bg-white p-4">
          <div class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-gray-500">Encryption at rest</div>
          <p class="mt-1">Authorization credentials are encrypted using industry-standard encryption.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-lg border border-gray-200 bg-white p-4">
          <div class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-gray-500">Encryption in transit</div>
          <p class="mt-1">All data transmissions are encrypted using HTTPS/TLS.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-lg border border-gray-200 bg-white p-4">
          <div class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-gray-500">Password security</div>
          <p class="mt-1">Passwords are cryptographically hashed and never stored in readable form.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-lg border border-gray-200 bg-white p-4">
          <div class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-gray-500">Access control</div>
          <p class="mt-1">Data is restricted per-account with role-based permissions and tenant isolation.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <p class="mt-4 text-xs text-gray-500">While we strive to protect your information, no method of electronic transmission or storage is completely secure. We cannot guarantee absolute security.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">Data retention</h2>
      <ul class="space-y-2 list-disc pl-5">
        <li>Account information is retained for as long as your account is active or as needed to provide services.</li>
        <li>Authorization credentials are deleted immediately when you disconnect your TikTok Shop.</li>
        <li>Campaign, invitation, and sample history is retained to support your business records and reporting needs. You may request deletion at any time.</li>
        <li>We may retain certain data as required by applicable law or for legitimate business purposes such as resolving disputes.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">Your rights</h2>
      <p class="mb-4">Depending on your jurisdiction, you may have the following rights regarding your personal information:</p>
      <div class="overflow-hidden rounded-lg border border-gray-200">
        <table class="min-w-full text-sm">
          <tbody class="divide-y divide-gray-100">
            <tr><td class="px-4 py-3 font-medium text-gray-900 w-36">Access</td><td class="px-4 py-3">Request a copy of the personal information we hold about you.</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="px-4 py-3 font-medium text-gray-900">Correction</td><td class="px-4 py-3">Request that we correct inaccurate or incomplete information.</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="px-4 py-3 font-medium text-gray-900">Deletion</td><td class="px-4 py-3">Request that we delete your personal information, subject to certain exceptions.</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="px-4 py-3 font-medium text-gray-900">Disconnect</td><td class="px-4 py-3">Revoke Tikedon's access to your TikTok Shop at any time, which immediately deletes stored authorization credentials.</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="px-4 py-3 font-medium text-gray-900">Portability</td><td class="px-4 py-3">Request an export of your data in a commonly used format.</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="px-4 py-3 font-medium text-gray-900">Withdraw consent</td><td class="px-4 py-3">Where processing is based on your consent, you may withdraw it at any time.</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
      <p class="mt-3">To exercise any of these rights, contact us using the information below.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">Cookies and tracking</h2>
      <p>Tikedon uses essential session cookies required for authentication and application functionality. We do not use third-party advertising cookies or tracking pixels. We do not use TikTok Pixel or any social media tracking tools on our application.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">Children's privacy</h2>
      <p>Tikedon is a business application intended for use by persons aged 18 and older. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 18. If we learn that we have collected information from a child under 18, we will delete it promptly.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">International data transfers</h2>
      <p>Your information is processed and stored in the United States. If you are accessing our services from outside the United States, your information will be transferred to, stored, and processed in the United States. By using our services, you consent to such transfer.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">Changes to this policy</h2>
      <p>We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of material changes by posting the updated policy on this page with a revised effective date. Your continued use of Tikedon after changes are posted constitutes your acceptance of the updated policy.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="rounded-lg border border-gray-200 bg-gray-50 p-6">
      <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">Contact us</h2>
      <p>If you have questions about this Privacy Policy, wish to exercise your data rights, or have a privacy concern, please contact us:</p>
      <p class="mt-3"><strong>Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:privacy@tikedon.com" class="text-indigo-600 hover:text-indigo-500">privacy@tikedon.com</a></p>
    </section>

  </div>
</div>
